I’ve been fostering this cute little guy. He came to me terrified and I’m not sure he’d ever had a human parent before. Every day brings him a bit more out of his shell. He’s timid but curious. I see evidence of a playful pup. He loves walks and other dogs. He’s docile and kind — would be a great family dog. And now he needs a forever home — someone who can keep doing the loving work to make him feel safe and secure so he doesn’t have to be afraid anymore. Sweet, sweet boy. 

They think he’s about one year old. He does not bite or snap or snarl — and when you’re able to get him in your lap for some love, you can feel how much he wants and needs it. 

Contact @wagmorpets if you’re interested in adopting Baxter.

He’s back! After three weeks in board and train (which is really just 3 weeks of learning how to be a dog and let yourself be held and loved), Chandler is ready to be adopted. He loves laps and a good party and other dogs. Has never once bared his teeth or tried to nip —- he’s cautious, as are all these former kill-list dogs who were neglected at the shelter where they spent their lives, but he’s showing all the signs of being a total love-bug.  Contact @wagmorpets to fill out an application.

Chandler is doing so well. He is a super chill little guy.  Loves to crawl into bed with you to cuddle. He’s still a little nervous around strangers and big dogs, but he loooooves all other dogs and he loves his treats and his naps. This week we’re going to learn how to teach him basic commands. Whoever adopts him is in for a lot of love and cuteness. Contact @wagmorpets if you’d like to meet him!
@wagmorpets —- help Chandler find his forever home!

Yep, we’re on strike. Been here before. It’s not fun, but solidarity can help us make history.

Sad but true. We’re in a pivotal moment in this industry where money people are standing in the way of creators getting paid fairly for their content. The dream of being a working writer and providing for a family in a meaningful way is in danger of becoming obsolete for many. Small changes can fix this, but not without a willingness to try. If writers can’t make improvements now at this critical juncture, then things will continue to get worse across all crafts in the business. Stand in solidarity if you’re able to. Thank you.
Had a nice TVDU reunion at the Radford gate today. Writers from all three shows walking the line together in solidarity. Loved seeing everyone.
Thank you for the birthday love. This one was really nice.

Hahaha just kidding. But a guilty-pleasure midday post picket cocktail with good friends is a nice by-product of an otherwise difficult situation.

🎥 made by: @qhiloh 

Chandler is a small dog lover’s dream. Small enough to travel, big enough to have swagger. He absolutely loves other dogs (except big dogs — somewhere in his past a big dog was not nice to him) and after a life lived in a bad situation, is really coming out of his shell. He’s learning to play and learning to trust. Once he understands that you’re no danger to him, he is full of love and cuddles. Loves to sleep by your side (or under your sheets, or on your head 😂). Definitely prefers women to men. If you’re willing to put in just a little bit of time helping him get settled (literally just a few days), he’ll be your perfect dog and best friend. We’ve recently started basic training and he’s picking it up beautifully. Knows how to come, stay and, most importantly, pee outside. @wagmorpets
visit www.tusctogether.com for more info

Chandler came to me terrified of people and the world. We’ve been working on all of that and I’m thrilled to say he’s a total lovebug. He’ll need a family who can be patient with him while he learns to open up, but I promise you he will and then you’ll get to benefit from all the love he’s ready to give. I’ll talk you through everything there is to know about him — all the good (so much) and also the areas where he still needs work (he’s still a little bit of a scaredycat). You will not regret adopting this guy. Plus I’ll stock you up with some food and toys to take with you!

He’s just over 1, mostly potty trained, has had basic obedience lessons, loves toys and play and naps and cuddles.

Best news. Chandler has found his forever home!! After six months of fostering, growing from a dog who wouldn’t come out from under the bed to one who frolics and naps and cuddles. He’s going to live a great life. Even better, he still gets to come over and play so I don’t have to say goodbye. Congratulations Chandler and @browneyedgal17 !!
